cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a deep learning model for click-through rate (CTR) prediction in web applications, which is a common task in online advertising and recommender systems. The model is based on graph neural networks (GNNs) and aims to model feature interactions among different feature fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to deep learning and neural networks. 

Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as CTR prediction is often used in search engines and recommendation systems, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a novel approach to modeling feature interactions, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the proposed model is based on a graph structure, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with multi-field features and their interactions.
